Gedeon Richter Nyrt. (RICHT)  rebounded from a
3 1/2-month low after the biggest drugmaker in Hungary said its
first-quarter profit jumped 50 percent from a year earlier.  The stock rose 1.4 percent to 36,610 forint by 9:30 a.m. in
Budapest, after sliding 3.6 percent in the previous two sessions
to the lowest price since Jan. 25. Todayâ€™s move made Richter the
